For Nigeria’s fast rising business Reality TV Show, The Legends, 2021 seems to be going on a high note, as leading brands in the Food and Cosmetics sectors in Nigeria have thrown their weight behind the project. Already, Checkers Africa Limited, makers of Checkers Custard, Emo Cosmetics and Perfumes Ltd and Vicmore Marketing Resources Limited have sealed partnership this year’s edition of the show scheduled to commence soon, as viewers await the official unveiling. The Legends is an African themed Reality TV Show that focuses on harnessing the stories of exploits, pains and gains of African business and career heroes to inspire its contestants and viewers towards making giant strides with their potentials in their fields of endeavour. Following its maiden edition last year amid the global pandemic, which aired on WAP TV on Dstv, Gotv, Startimes, Starsat, Playtv and Mytv, producing a winner who walked home with a grand Car prize, 1 N1million cash and one year endorsement by EMO Cosmetics, the show has grown in leaps and bound, with a growing viewers’ demand on TV screens in the Reality TV Entertainment sector of Nigeria. The season 2 is set make a deep statement and viral coversation amongst all lovers of reality TV show entertainment, as planning are currently underway to host nothing but the best in the second edition tagged HOT GANG, said the organisers, Delaquine Services. According to the head of programme for the show, the sealed partnerships are premised on the anticipated media mileage the show will avail to its supporting brands and the role it is playing towards youth development and nation building. The partnerships therefore will have Checkers Custard; Nigeria’s leading Custard Food, as the official breakfast partner of the show while EMO Cosmetics and Perfumes Limited and Vicmore Marketing Resources Limited as the official Fragrance and Body Care partners respectively. The management of the various brands have expressed their optimism in the show and the impact it will have on the youths’ wellbeing and also the growth of their businesses, while calling on all well meaning Nigerians to throw their weight behind the show while getting ready to watch the show by the time it kicks off. The organizers have also expressed their joy at the support of these brands and also beckon on all Nigerians, home and abroad to follow the show on all of its social media handles to get all updates regarding the date of commencement, other details while anticipating a very thrilling entertainment contents from the show which will hit their screens soonest. 